codata is a Fortran library providing the fundamental physical constants
published by CODATA. 
It includes the 2022, 2018, 2014 and 2010 recommended values, 
allowing applications to reproduce calculations based on specific 
CODATA releases.

- Documentation: https://milanskocic.github.io/codata/
- Man pages: https://github.com/MilanSkocic/codata/tree/main/docs/man
- Examples: https://github.com/MilanSkocic/codata/tree/main/example
- Source code: https://github.com/MilanSKocic/codata
- Binaries: https://github.com/MilanSkocic/codata/releases
- Python wrapper: https://pypi.org/project/pycodata

It provides:
- CODATA 2022 constants
- CODATA 2018 constants
- CODATA 2014 constants
- CODATA 2010 constants

For the installation instructions, see the INSTALL file.
